00:52:51.100 --> 00:52:52.790 align:middle line:90%
I just never believed that.

00:52:52.790 --> 00:52:55.300 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't about trampling
people as you went.

00:52:55.300 --> 00:52:59.920 align:middle line:84%
It was more about sort of
you kind of finding your way

00:52:59.920 --> 00:53:01.570 align:middle line:90%
and picking your spots.

00:53:01.570 --> 00:53:04.720 align:middle line:84%
And I just felt that you
had to be who you were,

00:53:04.720 --> 00:53:08.440 align:middle line:84%
and you had to want it, and
you had to use your intuition

00:53:08.440 --> 00:53:11.020 align:middle line:84%
and figure out how you
were going to get there.

00:53:11.020 --> 00:53:13.330 align:middle line:84%
>> I sit here now, and I
look at some of the 20--

00:53:13.330 --> 00:53:15.610 align:middle line:84%
or 20-somethings
and 30 somethings,

00:53:15.610 --> 00:53:17.170 align:middle line:90%
and they're the new generation.

00:53:17.170 --> 00:53:18.130 align:middle line:90%
There's a new wave.

00:53:18.130 --> 00:53:20.332 align:middle line:84%
They're not being brought
into the workforce saying,

00:53:20.332 --> 00:53:21.790 align:middle line:84%
as a woman, the
only way you can be

00:53:21.790 --> 00:53:24.890 align:middle line:84%
successful is to wear your
blue suit and red shirt.

00:53:24.890 --> 00:53:28.265 align:middle line:84%
>> Every day I come to work is
a reminder that we haven't done

00:53:28.265 --> 00:53:29.065 align:middle line:90%
enough.

00:53:29.065 --> 00:53:32.530 align:middle line:84%
I go to too many meetings in
which I'm the only female,

00:53:32.530 --> 00:53:35.350 align:middle line:84%
the only person of
color, the only person

00:53:35.350 --> 00:53:38.030 align:middle line:84%
from an underrepresented
group whatsoever.

00:53:38.030 --> 00:53:41.170 align:middle line:84%
I don't like it because it
really doesn't add value

00:53:41.170 --> 00:53:43.270 align:middle line:84%
to the product we're
building unless we really

00:53:43.270 --> 00:53:47.590 align:middle line:84%
have those diverse perspectives
and diverse ways of leading.

00:53:47.590 --> 00:53:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Just last year, I
was at a conference.

00:53:50.240 --> 00:53:52.030 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
my presentation,

00:53:52.030 --> 00:53:56.620 align:middle line:84%
a woman came, and she said,
you actually did a good job.

00:53:56.620 --> 00:53:58.730 align:middle line:90%
I was so impressed.

00:53:58.730 --> 00:54:00.620 align:middle line:90%
And it is a compliment.

00:54:00.620 --> 00:54:04.330 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, if I want
to translate it in my mind,

00:54:04.330 --> 00:54:09.400 align:middle line:84%
is, you're better than I thought
because I have this perception

00:54:09.400 --> 00:54:10.820 align:middle line:90%
of people like you.

00:54:10.820 --> 00:54:15.280 align:middle line:84%
You don't walk into a
presentation with a white male

00:54:15.280 --> 00:54:17.860 align:middle line:84%
