presentation and say,

00:54:17.860 --> 00:54:21.370 align:middle line:84%
I didn't expect you
to be doing this well.

00:54:21.370 --> 00:54:23.050 align:middle line:90%
Actually, you did a good job.

00:54:23.050 --> 00:54:27.590 align:middle line:84%
I constantly get those kinds
of comments from people.

00:54:27.590 --> 00:54:31.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Whether it's in athletics,
or whether it's in executive

00:54:31.270 --> 00:54:36.910 align:middle line:84%
positions in the business world,
or whether it's in artistry,

00:54:36.910 --> 00:54:41.380 align:middle line:84%
I think that there is just a
general opinion in society that

00:54:41.380 --> 00:54:43.390 align:middle line:90%
men do it better.

00:54:43.390 --> 00:54:47.840 align:middle line:84%
But just the fact that I have
been a female musical director

00:54:47.840 --> 00:54:53.960 align:middle line:84%
in a largely male-dominated
field speaks volumes.

00:54:53.960 --> 00:54:54.980 align:middle line:90%
Is it unequal?

00:54:54.980 --> 00:54:56.280 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it is.

00:54:56.280 --> 00:54:57.080 align:middle line:90%
Can you do it?

00:54:57.080 --> 00:54:58.870 align:middle line:90%
Yes, you can.

00:54:58.870 --> 00:55:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>> No matter what industry you
go into, you're going to have

00:55:01.390 --> 00:55:03.515 align:middle line:84%
your insecurities, you're
going to have challenges,

00:55:03.515 --> 00:55:05.598 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have the
