religious and holding

00:55:27.960 --> 00:55:30.910 align:middle line:84%
on to traditional
religious values.

00:55:30.910 --> 00:55:32.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm actually not doing that.

00:55:32.310 --> 00:55:35.220 align:middle line:84%
You know, I talk about, for
example, gay, lesbian rights,

00:55:35.220 --> 00:55:37.050 align:middle line:90%
and people go, what?

00:55:37.050 --> 00:55:38.360 align:middle line:90%
You are talking about that?

00:55:38.360 --> 00:55:40.080 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, yes.

00:55:40.080 --> 00:55:44.670 align:middle line:84%
You can be thinking differently
in different situations.

00:55:44.670 --> 00:55:47.310 align:middle line:84%
I call myself a Muslim
feminist because I

00:55:47.310 --> 00:55:51.570 align:middle line:84%
think Muslim women have been
extremely misunderstood.

00:55:51.570 --> 00:55:55.895 align:middle line:84%
My spouse is not
religious at all.

00:55:55.895 --> 00:55:57.520 align:middle line:84%
And from the beginning
of our marriage,

00:55:57.520 --> 00:55:59.790 align:middle line:84%
he has said, I
respect your decision,

00:55:59.790 --> 00:56:01.710 align:middle line:84%
how you want to
identify yourself,

00:56:01.710 --> 00:56:03.510 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not
identifying with this.

00:56:03.510 --> 00:56:06.930 align:middle line:84%
He says, people think
that I am an oppressor.

00:56:06.930 --> 00:56:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Actually, in reality,
you are oppressing me.

00:56:09.900 --> 00:56:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And so he says,
nobody talks about how

00:56:13.650 --> 00:56:16.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm oppressed by your
presence in different places.

00:56:16.800 --> 00:56:21.360 align:middle line:84%
But we still joke about it,
and he says, one of these days,

00:56:21.360 --> 00:56:23.580 align:middle line:84%
you're going to emancipate
yourself, right?

00:56:23.580 --> 00:56:25.270 align:middle line:84%
And I say, yeah, and
one of these days,

00:56:25.270 --> 00:56:26.520 align:middle line:90%
you're going to get it, right?

00:56:26.520 --> 00:56:30.090 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] That's
why I'm doing this.

00:56:30.090 --> 00:56:32.930 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, if I think back, I
was probably always a feminist.

00:56:32.930 --> 00:56:35.130 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I was
in the eighth grade,

00:56:35.130 --> 00:56:36.680 align:middle line:84%
and I had gone to
Catholic school.

00:56:36.680 --> 00:56:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And the group of girls that
were my friends at the time,

00:56:40.100 --> 00:56:43.580 align:middle line:84%
we were talking about who was
going to be class president.

00:56:43.580 --> 00:56:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And someone suggested one
of us, and someone else

00:56:46.070 --> 00:56:48.660 align:middle line:84%
said, oh, no, it
has to be a boy.

00:56:48.660 --> 00:56:50.150 align:middle line:84%
It's traditionally--
it's always--

00:56:50.150 --> 00:56:52.870 align:middle line:84%
and I remember
thinking, why, why, why?

00:56:52.870 --> 00:56:55.490 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] You know, I didn't
like that, but I didn't--

00:56:55.490 --> 00:56:57.980 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that I
said much about it then.

00:56:57.980 --> 00:57:05.420 align:middle line:84%
>> You just have this major
resistance to really supporting

00:57:05.420 --> 00:57:07.430 align:middle line:90%
powerful women.

00:57:07.430 --> 00:57:09.440 align:middle line:84%
We haven't even had a
female president yet.

00:57:09.440 --> 00:57:11.250 align:middle line:90%
It's crazy to me.

00:57:11.250 --> 00:57:14.640 align:middle line:84%
Like, I wanted to see a
government that's at least

00:57:14.640 --> 00:57:17.185 align:middle line:90%
half women, at least half.

00:57:17.185 --> 00:57:22.130 align:middle line:90%


00:57:22.130 --> 00:57:24.950 align:middle line:84%
>> So even the movies, and
the industries, and the media,

00:57:24.950 --> 00:57:28.940 align:middle line:84%
