01:12:28.625 --> 01:12:29.425 align:middle line:90%
beautiful.

01:12:29.425 --> 01:12:30.705 align:middle line:90%
We all deserve amazing.

01:12:30.705 --> 01:12:33.652 align:middle line:90%
We all deserve wonderful.

01:12:33.652 --> 01:12:35.110 align:middle line:84%
When you're parenting
children that

01:12:35.110 --> 01:12:37.570 align:middle line:84%
have extreme trauma
and attachment issues,

01:12:37.570 --> 01:12:39.490 align:middle line:90%
you're constantly rejected.

01:12:39.490 --> 01:12:41.740 align:middle line:84%
It brings up the past things
that you've gone through.

01:12:41.740 --> 01:12:43.840 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know, I
want to be angry at it,

01:12:43.840 --> 01:12:46.240 align:middle line:84%
but really it is me
interpreting rejection

01:12:46.240 --> 01:12:47.790 align:middle line:90%
that maybe I felt as a child.

01:12:47.790 --> 01:12:50.515 align:middle line:84%
Or your lack of being
capable of doing something

01:12:50.515 --> 01:12:52.420 align:middle line:84%
may be really a
fear that I still

01:12:52.420 --> 01:12:54.460 align:middle line:84%
have as a grown adult
that I can't do it,

01:12:54.460 --> 01:12:58.470 align:middle line:84%
and being able to recognize
where my shortcomings are,

01:12:58.470 --> 01:13:01.000 align:middle line:84%
and healing those in order
for me to be able to catch

01:13:01.000 --> 01:13:03.800 align:middle line:90%
my kids when they fall.

01:13:03.800 --> 01:13:06.055 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times when
things are really cruddy,

01:13:06.055 --> 01:13:08.582 align:middle line:84%
or someone's throwing
a tantrum, we dance.

01:13:08.582 --> 01:13:11.275 align:middle line:84%
We dance with it instead
of reveling in it.

01:13:11.275 --> 01:13:12.650 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
that's something

01:13:12.650 --> 01:13:15.410 align:middle line:84%
that my kids have
taught me because life's

01:13:15.410 --> 01:13:17.690 align:middle line:84%
too short to roll around
in it, so you might as well

01:13:17.690 --> 01:13:18.490 align:middle line:90%
just dance.

01:13:18.490 --> 01:13:21.080 align:middle line:90%
[PEACEFUL MUSIC]

01:13:21.080 --> 01:13:28.110 align:middle line:84%
>> I really didn't get the
full scope of what it is to be

01:13:28.110 --> 01:13:31.670 align:middle line:90%
locked, to be so disoriented.

01:13:31.670 --> 01:13:36.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's what my daughter
brought me because she really

01:13:36.930 --> 01:13:38.360 align:middle line:90%
didn't sleep.

01:13:38.360 --> 01:13:41.760 align:middle line:84%
The more unbelievably
hard it got,

01:13:41.760 --> 01:13:47.310 align:middle line:84%
the more I learned to just
give over to this experience

01:13:47.310 --> 01:13:49.400 align:middle line:90%
and not be in control.

01:13:49.400 --> 01:13:57.145 align:middle line:84%
I was so driven by being
perceived as important.

01:13:57.145 --> 01:13:59.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm a public radio producer.

01:13:59.110 --> 01:14:01.660 align:middle line:84%
My work gets
nationally distributed.

01:14:01.660 --> 01:14:03.040 align:middle line:90%
I'm award-winning.

01:14:03.040 --> 01:14:05.860 align:middle line:90%


01:14:05.860 --> 01:14:08.680 align:middle line:84%
My daughter didn't
give a crap about that.

01:14:08.680 --> 01:14:11.170 align:middle line:84%
It was like the
little part of me

01:14:11.170 --> 01:14:13.250 align:middle line:84%
that didn't feel smart
when I was growing up,

01:14:13.250 --> 01:14:16.060 align:middle line:84%
or didn't feel good enough,
that somehow my career was

01:14:16.060 --> 01:14:18.940 align:middle line:90%
going to satiate that wound.

01:14:18.940 --> 01:14:21.280 align:middle line:84%
I just really learned
that the woman

01:14:21.280 --> 01:14:26.140 align:middle line:84%
that I'm here to become for
my daughter needs to be solid.

01:14:26.140 --> 01:14:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And if I am really scared
underneath my armor of success,

01:14:33.470 --> 01:14:37.160 align:middle line:84%
then it's a house of
cards because, in my home,

01:14:37.160 --> 01:14:39.273 align:middle line:90%
my kids really see who I am.

01:14:39.273 --> 01:14:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And no matter what
happens, they love me

01:14:43.020 --> 01:14:46.140 align:middle line:90%
because I'm showing up here.

01:14:46.140 --> 01:14:49.950 align:middle line:84%
>> I spent the last 25
years raising my kids,

01:14:49.950 --> 01:14:52.080 align:middle line:90%
and that was my priority.

01:14:52.080 --> 01:14:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And now, they're
grown, and I decided

01:14:56.460 --> 01:14:58.320 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to
go back to school

01:14:58.320 --> 01:15:02.100 align:middle line:84%
and try to become a
professional baker.

01:15:02.100 --> 01:15:04.877 align:middle line:90%
It was very scary at first.

01:15:04.877 --> 01:15:06.460 align:middle line:84%
I thought, oh my
gosh, I'm going to be

01:15:06.460 --> 01:15:08.520 align:middle line:90%
the oldest one in the class.

01:15:08.520 --> 01:15:12.790 align:middle line:84%
But I got past that
first day and realized,

01:15:12.790 --> 01:15:15.360 align:middle line:84%
gosh, there's a lot of
people my age in the class,

01:15:15.360 --> 01:15:18.958 align:middle line:90%
and they feel the same way.

01:15:18.958 --> 01:15:21.000 align:middle line:84%
If there's something you
need to do in your life,

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:22.875 align:middle line:84%
and you want to do it,
you could still do it.

01:15:22.875 --> 01:15:25.050 align:middle line:84%
You could still
raise your children.

01:15:25.050 --> 01:15:28.020 align:middle line:84%
If you decide you want
to go back to work,

01:15:28.020 --> 01:15:30.690 align:middle line:84%
if you decide you want
to go back to school,

01:15:30.690 --> 01:15:32.250 align:middle line:90%
you could definitely do it.

01:15:32.250 --> 01:15:36.010 align:middle line:84%
And you'll be a much better
person for your children

01:15:36.010 --> 01:15:36.810 align:middle line:90%
if you're happier.

01:15:36.810 --> 01:15:39.330 align:middle line:90%


01:15:39.330 --> 01:15:42.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Whether it's through
choosing to have a child or not,

01:15:42.450 --> 01:15:45.810 align:middle line:84%
choosing to plant that garden,
there is something that is

01:15:45.810 --> 01:15:50.260 align:middle line:84%
so potent in that
ability to give life.

01:15:50.260 --> 01:15:52.060 align:middle line:84%
And I chose not
to have children,

01:15:52.060 --> 01:15:57.354 align:middle line:84%
and yet, it's not that I didn't
become a mother in my own way.

01:15:57.354 --> 01:15:59.460 align:middle line:84%
There are things
that I mothered,

01:15:59.460 --> 01:16:01.830 align:middle line:84%
people that I mothered,
projects that I mothered,

01:16:01.830 --> 01:16:05.940 align:middle line:84%
and so that, it is that ability
to give life and nurture it.

01:16:05.940 --> 01:16:10.590 align:middle line:84%
>> We do have unique callings,
and there's no degradation

01:16:10.590 --> 01:16:13.320 align:middle line:84%
of the woman whose
calling is to be a mother.

01:16:13.320 --> 01:16:15.360 align:middle line:84%
That's every bit as
valid as the woman

01:16:15.360 --> 01:16:18.330 align:middle line:84%
who wants to be the
next Oprah Winfrey.

01:16:18.330 --> 01:16:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And if you have
no desire to have

01:16:21.600 --> 01:16:24.020 align:middle line:84%
an actual child
in this lifetime,

01:16:24.020 --> 01:16:25.890 align:middle line:84%
but you have all of
this other inspiration--

01:16:25.890 --> 01:16:27.210 align:middle line:90%
[CHILD YELLING]

01:16:27.210 --> 01:16:33.063 align:middle line:84%
--that you want to do,
that's valid as well.

01:16:33.063 --> 01:16:34.230 align:middle line:90%
>> I want to leave a legacy.

01:16:34.230 --> 01:16:35.100 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - ANGELA CAROLE BROWN,
 "TICKET HOME"]

01:16:35.100 --> 01:16:36.570 align:middle line:90%
I don't have children.

01:16:36.570 --> 01:16:38.040 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a husband.

01:16:38.040 --> 01:16:40.050 align:middle line:84%
I don't have that
kind of family.

01:16:40.050 --> 01:16:43.650 align:middle line:84%
So for me, you know,
my legacy is my art.

01:16:43.650 --> 01:16:45.150 align:middle line:90%
(SINGING) And there's no--

01:16:45.150 --> 01:16:50.088 align:middle line:84%
And I believe I was put here to
contribute that to the world,

01:16:50.088 --> 01:16:51.630 align:middle line:84%
you know, something
that outlives me.

01:16:51.630 --> 01:17:00.625 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Maybe then you
can find your ticket home.

01:17:00.625 --> 01:17:03.650 align:middle line:90%


01:17:03.650 --> 01:17:06.930 align:middle line:84%
>> We learned so early
in our lives that,

01:17:06.930 --> 01:17:08.880 align:middle line:84%
if you're not doing
certain types of activity,

01:17:08.880 --> 01:17:11.260 align:middle line:84%
then you're not part
of the creative group.

01:17:11.260 --> 01:17:13.320 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing how
you can limit yourself

01:17:13.320 --> 01:17:15.480 align:middle line:84%
when you think that
you're not allowed to play

01:17:15.480 --> 01:17:17.610 align:middle line:90%
in that part of the playground.

01:17:17.610 --> 01:17:18.960 align:middle line:90%
>> There is so much--

01:17:18.960 --> 01:17:23.050 align:middle line:84%
so many forces, not just from
parents, but from schools,

01:17:23.050 --> 01:17:29.220 align:middle line:84%
from society, that that
childhood dream-like excitement

01:17:29.220 --> 01:17:33.210 align:middle line:84%
starts getting squished
and stifled and stifled,

01:17:33.210 --> 01:17:38.895 align:middle line:84%
and then we start to accept
the beliefs of the world.

01:17:38.895 --> 01:17:40.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, to be successful,
you've got to have

01:17:40.770 --> 01:17:42.870 align:middle line:84%
a high-paying job, so
you can have a big house.

01:17:42.870 --> 01:17:45.107 align:middle line:84%
>> And have a mortgage
and 2.5 children.

01:17:45.107 --> 01:17:46.690 align:middle line:84%
>> That you're
supposed to have a job,

01:17:46.690 --> 01:17:48.385 align:middle line:90%
that you work these hours.

01:17:48.385 --> 01:17:50.130 align:middle line:90%
>> You pay the rent.

01:17:50.130 --> 01:17:52.320 align:middle line:84%
You get the salaries
coming every month.

01:17:52.320 --> 01:17:56.430 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's like all the stuff
and all the context take away

01:17:56.430 --> 01:17:57.625 align:middle line:90%
your options.

01:17:57.625 --> 01:17:59.250 align:middle line:84%
>> This is where you
fit in this world,

01:17:59.250 --> 01:18:02.010 align:middle line:84%
and you don't belong anywhere
else, so don't even try.

01:18:02.010 --> 01:18:05.400 align:middle line:84%
Those are messages that I
know we're bombarded with.

01:18:05.400 --> 01:18:11.070 align:middle line:84%
>> How am I supposed to fit this
who-I-am-ness into that box?

01:18:11.070 --> 01:18:12.687 align:middle line:90%
And where did the box come from?

01:18:12.687 --> 01:18:15.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Somebody said the other day
to me, she said something like,

01:18:15.270 --> 01:18:16.210 align:middle line:90%
oh, so how do you make money?

01:18:16.210 --> 01:18:16.960 align:middle line:84%
I was like, you
know, I make clothes.

01:18:16.960 --> 01:18:17.750 align:middle line:84%
She said, that's
how you survive?

01:18:17.750 --> 01:18:20.130 align:middle line:84%
I said, no, I don't survive
off of making clothes.

01:18:20.130 --> 01:18:21.160 align:middle line:90%
I live off of it.

01:18:21.160 --> 01:18:23.400 align:middle line:84%
We didn't come here
to just suffer.

01:18:23.400 --> 01:18:24.630 align:middle line:90%
We came here to learn.

01:18:24.630 --> 01:18:26.463 align:middle line:84%
We came here to experience,
and we came here

01:18:26.463 --> 01:18:27.390 align:middle line:90%
to live in abundance.

01:18:27.390 --> 01:18:33.870 align:middle line:84%
>> We really are misguided in
the world about what's valuable

01:18:33.870 --> 01:18:36.100 align:middle line:90%
and what's possible.

01:18:36.100 --> 01:18:38.780 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot of
great, creative energy

01:18:38.780 --> 01:18:40.160 align:middle line:90%
is wasted that way.

01:18:40.160 --> 01:18:42.260 align:middle line:84%
>> It's important to
have a vision, like,

01:18:42.260 --> 01:18:47.180 align:middle line:84%
a clear vision of what you
want and of who you want to be.

01:18:47.180 --> 01:18:50.330 align:middle line:84%
I have to do a lot of
self-encouraging, which

01:18:50.330 --> 01:18:53.230 align:middle line:84%
is pretty exhausting at times,
but I think that a lot of women

01:18:53.230 --> 01:18:54.390 align:middle line:90%
have to do that.

01:18:54.390 --> 01:18:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And then, women
of color or people

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:57.890 align:middle line:84%
who are gay, women
who are queer, too,

01:18:57.890 --> 01:19:00.860 align:middle line:84%
just, like, you have to do that
more and more with each added

01:19:00.860 --> 01:19:03.260 align:middle line:90%
oppression.

01:19:03.260 --> 01:19:04.865 align:middle line:84%
Right now, a lot
of other people are

01:19:04.865 --> 01:19:06.860 align:middle line:84%
at those same crossroads
where they're not

01:19:06.860 --> 01:19:11.480 align:middle line:84%
fitting into any specific
categories of what, you know,

01:19:11.480 --> 01:19:13.230 align:middle line:84%
you're supposed to do,
depending on, like,

01:19:13.230 --> 01:19:16.850 align:middle line:84%
your gender or your
race or your sexuality.

01:19:16.850 --> 01:19:18.320 align:middle line:84%
I feel like, in
the world, there's

01:19:18.320 --> 01:19:22.310 align:middle line:84%
not that many visual
images of women

01:19:22.310 --> 01:19:25.100 align:middle line:84%
of color in all different
aspects of life,

01:19:25.100 --> 01:19:28.200 align:middle line:84%
and so I'm trying to just
make that readily available

01:19:28.200 --> 01:19:29.000 align:middle line:90%
for people.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:31.250 align:middle line:84%
I just feel like it's
important to have

01:19:31.250 --> 01:19:33.110 align:middle line:90%
people be able to see themself.

01:19:33.110 --> 01:19:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Mainstream media and art
doesn't really do that.

01:19:35.730 --> 01:19:38.350 align:middle line:90%


01:19:38.350 --> 01:19:40.570 align:middle line:84%
>> I think women are
lacking representation,

01:19:40.570 --> 01:19:43.637 align:middle line:84%
and I think I will just
have a lot of work to do.

01:19:43.637 --> 01:19:45.220 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's why I'm
here in New York,

01:19:45.220 --> 01:19:48.440 align:middle line:84%
and that's why I'm
a photographer.

01:19:48.440 --> 01:19:50.460 align:middle line:84%
The idea of creating
this goddess

01:19:50.460 --> 01:19:55.390 align:middle line:84%
is actually to create
a future for woman.

01:19:55.390 --> 01:19:59.480 align:middle line:84%
What kind of woman we want
to be, what kind of woman

01:19:59.480 --> 01:20:00.835 align:middle line:90%
we want to see.

01:20:00.835 --> 01:20:06.700 align:middle line:84%
She can be as strong as a
man, sensitive like a kid,

01:20:06.700 --> 01:20:12.120 align:middle line:84%
emotional like a woman, and
combine those things together,

01:20:12.120 --> 01:20:14.030 align:middle line:84%
she will become a
different vision

01:20:14.030 --> 01:20:15.380 align:middle line:90%
of the woman of the future.

01:20:15.380 --> 01:20:18.430 align:middle line:90%
[JAZZ-FUNK MUSIC]

01:20:18.430 --> 01:20:19.230 align:middle line:90%


01:20:19.230 --> 01:20:20.720 align:middle line:90%
>> I am a metal sculptor.

01:20:20.720 --> 01:20:25.100 align:middle line:84%
I sustain myself solely on
the metalwork that I do.

01:20:25.100 --> 01:20:28.340 align:middle line:84%
The underlying concept
in my sculpture

01:20:28.340 --> 01:20:35.870 align:middle line:84%
would be that metal is a pretty
rigid, masculine material,

01:20:35.870 --> 01:20:39.050 align:middle line:84%
so I try to bend it and make
it look a little bit more

01:20:39.050 --> 01:20:41.270 align:middle line:90%
like fabric, or organic.

01:20:41.270 --> 01:20:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking to
bring girl to the metal.

01:20:47.480 --> 01:20:50.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Fire art, metal art is
not a female-friendly field

01:20:50.870 --> 01:20:54.050 align:middle line:84%
in general, and so that is a
large part of what we tried

01:20:54.050 --> 01:20:57.950 align:middle line:84%
to create here is a space where
women feel empowered to do

01:20:57.950 --> 01:21:00.050 align:middle line:84%
something they've
never done before.

01:21:00.050 --> 01:21:03.140 align:middle line:84%
>> When you look at these
sculptures that we make,

01:21:03.140 --> 01:21:06.350 align:middle line:84%
it looks like you have to
be really tough to make this

01:21:06.350 --> 01:21:07.150 align:middle line:90%
thing.

01:21:07.150 --> 01:21:10.880 align:middle line:84%
But it's less about
physical strength,

01:21:10.880 --> 01:21:14.410 align:middle line:84%
but it's more about being
smart with your body

01:21:14.410 --> 01:21:15.900 align:middle line:90%
and smart about the tools.

01:21:15.900 --> 01:21:19.580 align:middle line:84%
You know, I don't have to be
a big, tough guy to do that.

01:21:19.580 --> 01:21:23.090 align:middle line:84%
>> I do think you can do a lot
by putting your mind to things,

01:21:23.090 --> 01:21:27.138 align:middle line:84%
but, you know, it doesn't
negate all of the class and race

01:21:27.138 --> 01:21:28.430 align:middle line:90%
issues we have in this country.

01:21:28.430 --> 01:21:32.020 align:middle line:84%
But it sure helps, and it's not
a bad way to live your life,

01:21:32.020 --> 01:21:34.940 align:middle line:84%
is focusing on what you do want
to do and believing you can do

01:21:34.940 --> 01:21:36.470 align:middle line:90%
it.

01:21:36.470 --> 01:21:41.150 align:middle line:90%
>> I said, OK, what do I want?

01:21:41.150 --> 01:21:42.920 align:middle line:90%
I want to write.

01:21:42.920 --> 01:21:46.650 align:middle line:84%
I want to be a writer,
and, you know, I was like--

01:21:46.650 --> 01:21:48.716 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to vomit,
like, I just felt like--

01:21:48.716 --> 01:21:50.757 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] OK, now I've said it.

01:21:50.757 --> 01:21:53.090 align:middle line:84%
Now I have to do
something with this.

01:21:53.090 --> 01:21:53.890 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

01:21:53.890 --> 01:21:57.295 align:middle line:84%
I would spend a
year being a writer.

01:21:57.295 --> 01:22:00.460 align:middle line:84%
If I can do this
on my own, then I

01:22:00.460 --> 01:22:02.920 align:middle line:84%
can prove to myself
that this is for real.

01:22:02.920 --> 01:22:06.150 align:middle line:84%
Within a few weeks,
I had started a blog.

01:22:06.150 --> 01:22:07.850 align:middle line:90%
I started a writers' group.

01:22:07.850 --> 01:22:12.880 align:middle line:84%
Then, you know, these
small acts of intention

01:22:12.880 --> 01:22:15.650 align:middle line:84%
behind this dream that I
just declared one night

01:22:15.650 --> 01:22:18.610 align:middle line:90%
started to become momentum.

01:22:18.610 --> 01:22:21.970 align:middle line:84%
>> If you show up for work every
day, no matter how you feel,

01:22:21.970 --> 01:22:26.920 align:middle line:84%
then the muses say, OK,
you're showing up for work.

01:22:26.920 --> 01:22:30.123 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to let
you be part of that world.

01:22:30.123 --> 01:22:31.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Even if you
choose, like, well,

01:22:31.540 --> 01:22:34.450 align:middle line:84%
that's not really what I
want to pursue as a career,

01:22:34.450 --> 01:22:38.077 align:middle line:84%
if it's something that's in
you, you got to do it always,

01:22:38.077 --> 01:22:40.660 align:middle line:84%
even if you're not trying to put
it out there in a public way,

01:22:40.660 --> 01:22:43.560 align:middle line:84%
just doing it for
the sake of soul.

