up every morning and finding

01:25:23.020 --> 01:25:24.040 align:middle line:90%
a reason to do that.

01:25:24.040 --> 01:25:27.010 align:middle line:84%
So it's a constant seeking
and searching kind of process

01:25:27.010 --> 01:25:28.243 align:middle line:90%
that you wake up.

01:25:28.243 --> 01:25:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And even if you're in
the most desperate mood,

01:25:30.160 --> 01:25:31.868 align:middle line:84%
you still wake up,
and lay there, and go,

01:25:31.868 --> 01:25:35.302 align:middle line:84%
OK, think of one good
reason to get up.

01:25:35.302 --> 01:25:36.260 align:middle line:90%
I don't know-- waffles.

01:25:36.260 --> 01:25:38.390 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:25:38.390 --> 01:25:40.170 align:middle line:84%
And I don't care if
it's a bad reason.

01:25:40.170 --> 01:25:41.200 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if
it's like, I can't

01:25:41.200 --> 01:25:43.200 align:middle line:84%
wait to have that first
cigarette, you know,

01:25:43.200 --> 01:25:45.070 align:middle line:84%
it's still going to
get you up out of bed

01:25:45.070 --> 01:25:46.360 align:middle line:90%
and moving through your life.

01:25:46.360 --> 01:25:47.830 align:middle line:84%
And then you've
got an opportunity

01:25:47.830 --> 01:25:51.100 align:middle line:84%
to make a difference in people's
lives, or at least to just

01:25:51.100 --> 01:25:53.470 align:middle line:84%
to have a thought
that makes you happy

01:25:53.470 --> 01:25:55.660 align:middle line:84%
or have a smile,
to see a rainbow.

01:25:55.660 --> 01:25:57.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I know that
sounds cheesy as all hell,

01:25:57.700 --> 01:26:00.190 align:middle line:84%
but seriously, it's
still fabulous.

01:26:00.190 --> 01:26:02.800 align:middle line:84%
>> It's so important that,
no matter what you're doing,

01:26:02.800 --> 01:26:05.470 align:middle line:84%
even when you feel like
you're doing something wrong,

01:26:05.470 --> 01:26:09.325 align:middle line:84%
that you approve of yourself
because if you don't approve

01:26:09.325 --> 01:26:11.590 align:middle line:84%
of yourself, no one
else is going to.

01:26:11.590 --> 01:26:15.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Everyone has
their insecurities.

01:26:15.360 --> 01:26:16.410 align:middle line:90%
It's the truth.

01:26:16.410 --> 01:26:17.370 align:middle line:90%
It's real.

01:26:17.370 --> 01:26:18.510 align:middle line:90%
We all have our faults.

01:26:18.510 --> 01:26:19.890 align:middle line:90%
We all have our flaws.

01:26:19.890 --> 01:26:23.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, we've all made
mistakes in our lives,

01:26:23.050 --> 01:26:25.980 align:middle line:84%
but if we could just pick
ourselves up and just

01:26:25.980 --> 01:26:29.350 align:middle line:84%
realize that it's evolution
that will never actually end.

01:26:29.350 --> 01:26:31.871 align:middle line:84%
We are always going
to be growing.

01:26:31.871 --> 01:26:34.340 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, flowers
are not always blooming.

01:26:34.340 --> 01:26:35.670 align:middle line:90%
She loses her leaves.

01:26:35.670 --> 01:26:37.020 align:middle line:90%
She loses her petals.

01:26:37.020 --> 01:26:39.000 align:middle line:90%
She roots more strongly.

01:26:39.000 --> 01:26:40.520 align:middle line:90%
She grows the next year.

01:26:40.520 --> 01:26:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And her scent never
smells the same.

01:26:42.180 --> 01:26:46.436 align:middle line:84%
So what she's creating,
her essence, her power,

01:26:46.436 --> 01:26:47.920 align:middle line:90%
is always different.

01:26:47.920 --> 01:26:50.070 align:middle line:90%
She's always in transformation.

01:26:50.070 --> 01:26:53.180 align:middle line:84%
>> As women, we need to believe
in ourselves and our abilities

01:26:53.180 --> 01:26:59.010 align:middle line:84%
to contribute more and value
everything we do in terms

01:26:59.010 --> 01:27:00.740 align:middle line:90%
of contributing to society.

01:27:00.740 --> 01:27:05.670 align:middle line:84%
We need to look at the
opportunities we have in life,

01:27:05.670 --> 01:27:08.400 align:middle line:84%
and use the
multi-dimensional thinking

01:27:08.400 --> 01:27:10.900 align:middle line:84%
that women have
in our advantage,

01:27:10.900 --> 01:27:13.540 align:middle line:84%
and change the
society for better.

01:27:13.540 --> 01:27:15.900 align:middle line:84%
>> A lot of oppression is
getting people to feel that

01:27:15.900 --> 01:27:18.010 align:middle line:84%
they can't do anything
for themselves.

01:27:18.010 --> 01:27:20.080 align:middle line:84%
Once we collectively
get over that,

01:27:20.080 --> 01:27:22.560 align:middle line:84%
it will be really
good for us all.

01:27:22.560 --> 01:27:24.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, there are things
that suck out there.

01:27:24.930 --> 01:27:30.230 align:middle line:84%
Yes, I hate the politics
and the politricks.

01:27:30.230 --> 01:27:31.680 align:middle line:90%
I want to acknowledge it.

01:27:31.680 --> 01:27:32.935 align:middle line:90%
I want to talk about it.

01:27:32.935 --> 01:27:35.910 align:middle line:84%
I want to wake people up,
and I don't want to sit in it

01:27:35.910 --> 01:27:37.420 align:middle line:90%
and marinate in it.

01:27:37.420 --> 01:27:41.280 align:middle line:84%
>> The key is to find all of
the good stuff and give that

01:27:41.280 --> 01:27:43.050 align:middle line:90%
as much of a presence.

01:27:43.050 --> 01:27:48.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Those of us that are trying
to be advocates and think about

01:27:48.300 --> 01:27:50.520 align:middle line:84%
social justice, we
have to be hopeful.

01:27:50.520 --> 01:27:52.470 align:middle line:84%
Look at the strengths
instead of weaknesses

01:27:52.470 --> 01:27:54.530 align:middle line:84%
because if we want to look
at what's not working,

01:27:54.530 --> 01:27:56.220 align:middle line:84%
there are a lot of
things not working.

01:27:56.220 --> 01:27:57.910 align:middle line:84%
But if you look
at what's working,

01:27:57.910 --> 01:27:59.970 align:middle line:84%
there are a lot of
projects and people

01:27:59.970 --> 01:28:01.940 align:middle line:84%
that are advocating
for differences.

01:28:01.940 --> 01:28:05.880 align:middle line:84%
So I'm hoping we all continue
to be passionate about what

01:28:05.880 --> 01:28:07.560 align:middle line:90%
we believe in.

01:28:07.560 --> 01:28:11.750 align:middle line:84%
>> You don't help someone who's
sick by being part of the sick.

01:28:11.750 --> 01:28:13.950 align:middle line:84%
You don't help people who
are afraid by becoming

01:28:13.950 --> 01:28:15.580 align:middle line:90%
part of the fearful.

01:28:15.580 --> 01:28:18.740 align:middle line:84%
We can be part of the
solution by not creating

01:28:18.740 --> 01:28:23.130 align:middle line:84%
a fertile ground for the racism,
and the homophobia, and all

01:28:23.130 --> 01:28:25.860 align:middle line:84%
the rest of it to
have much foothold.

01:28:25.860 --> 01:28:29.100 align:middle line:90%
That is the job of each person.

01:28:29.100 --> 01:28:31.690 align:middle line:84%
If you can at least keep
your spirit up for the day,

01:28:31.690 --> 01:28:33.550 align:middle line:90%
you've done a big thing.

01:28:33.550 --> 01:28:38.460 align:middle line:84%
>> It's we as a people rising
to recognize that we have

01:28:38.460 --> 01:28:41.670 align:middle line:84%
the ability to respond
to everything around us,

01:28:41.670 --> 01:28:45.960 align:middle line:84%
starting with ourselves
and moving out from there.

01:28:45.960 --> 01:28:47.862 align:middle line:84%
>> Your life is
really in your hands.

01:28:47.862 --> 01:28:50.070 align:middle line:84%
And no matter what you've
been taught, no matter what

01:28:50.070 --> 01:28:53.330 align:middle line:84%
you've been exposed to,
at the end of the day,

01:28:53.330 --> 01:28:54.240 align:middle line:90%
it's you, sister.

01:28:54.240 --> 01:28:57.691 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:28:57.691 --> 01:29:02.140 align:middle line:90%


01:29:02.140 --> 01:29:04.660 align:middle line:84%
>> At the end of our road
trip across the United States,

01:29:04.660 --> 01:29:07.960 align:middle line:84%
we shot over 300 hours of
footage and visited 30 states

01:29:07.960 --> 01:29:11.740 align:middle line:84%
in search of women
from all walks of life.

01:29:11.740 --> 01:29:14.010 align:middle line:84%
We lived out of the
Goddess Bus for six months

01:29:14.010 --> 01:29:18.540 align:middle line:84%
and ran it on recycled
vegetable oil whenever possible.

01:29:18.540 --> 01:29:21.240 align:middle line:84%
The vehicle had a bed,
five drawers, and cabinets

01:29:21.240 --> 01:29:24.340 align:middle line:90%
to hold dry food and equipment.

01:29:24.340 --> 01:29:27.010 align:middle line:84%
Living without amenities in
the hot summer on a budget

01:29:27.010 --> 01:29:30.470 align:middle line:90%
proved to be a challenge.

01:29:30.470 --> 01:29:33.210 align:middle line:84%
We worked out of coffee shops
and the dinner tables of kind

01:29:33.210 --> 01:29:35.780 align:middle line:84%
strangers and learned how
to interview and film women

01:29:35.780 --> 01:29:38.170 align:middle line:90%
as we went.

01:29:38.170 --> 01:29:41.200 align:middle line:84%
We sat down with artists,
mothers, healers,

01:29:41.200 --> 01:29:43.060 align:middle line:84%
businesswomen, and
scholars and discussed

01:29:43.060 --> 01:29:46.515 align:middle line:84%
what shaped them to
become who they are today.

01:29:46.515 --> 01:29:48.890 align:middle line:84%
Although each of their lives
were so different from ours,

01:29:48.890 --> 01:29:51.730 align:middle line:84%
we saw parts of ourselves
in all of these women.

01:29:51.730 --> 01:29:53.560 align:middle line:84%
Hearing their stories
bridged the gaps

01:29:53.560 --> 01:29:55.390 align:middle line:84%
between our differences
and showed us

01:29:55.390 --> 01:29:58.870 align:middle line:84%
how similar many of our
struggles really are.

01:29:58.870 --> 01:30:00.520 align:middle line:84%
Honoring the goddess
is not about what

01:30:00.520 --> 01:30:02.710 align:middle line:84%
you look like or
do for a living,

01:30:02.710 --> 01:30:05.080 align:middle line:84%
but about celebrating the
experience of womanhood,

01:30:05.080 --> 01:30:08.350 align:middle line:84%
finding what brings you joy,
and making a positive impact

01:30:08.350 --> 01:30:10.430 align:middle line:90%
on the world around you.

01:30:10.430 --> 01:30:13.490 align:middle line:84%
We met women who were passionate
about building self-esteem,

01:30:13.490 --> 01:30:17.290 align:middle line:84%
satellites, companies, families,
and everything in between.

01:30:17.290 --> 01:30:19.970 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, we realized
that the true power of women

01:30:19.970 --> 01:30:23.940 align:middle line:84%
is our ability to
create and nurture.

01:30:23.940 --> 01:30:25.700 align:middle line:84%
The women in this
film have shown us

01:30:25.700 --> 01:30:27.770 align:middle line:84%
that, with vision,
love, and resilience,

01:30:27.770 --> 01:30:29.990 align:middle line:84%
we can overcome
obstacles and give birth

01:30:29.990 --> 01:30:32.610 align:middle line:90%
to the life of our dreams.

01:30:32.610 --> 01:30:36.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Whether it is journeying
down to the depths of your own

01:30:36.050 --> 01:30:39.890 align:middle line:84%
shadow and unearthing the light
or giving birth to a creative

01:30:39.890 --> 01:30:42.980 align:middle line:84%
project, the journey you
go through to get there is

01:30:42.980 --> 01:30:47.000 align:middle line:84%
mirrored in the process of
actual physical childbirth.

01:30:47.000 --> 01:30:52.310 align:middle line:84%
Before a child is conceived,
ideally, a woman's body

01:30:52.310 --> 01:30:55.130 align:middle line:84%
is cleansed of any
toxins, and she's

01:30:55.130 --> 01:30:57.920 align:middle line:84%
getting really good
nutrition, and she's

01:30:57.920 --> 01:31:00.350 align:middle line:84%
come to a space
inside of herself

01:31:00.350 --> 01:31:04.310 align:middle line:84%
emotionally where she knows
who she is and feels fulfilled

01:31:04.310 --> 01:31:07.610 align:middle line:84%
in her life, so that
when she does take

01:31:07.610 --> 01:31:09.050 align:middle line:84%
on the creation
of this new life,

01:31:09.050 --> 01:31:11.730 align:middle line:90%
she's giving from the overflow.

01:31:11.730 --> 01:31:15.470 align:middle line:84%
So the first step is
eliminating any distractions,

01:31:15.470 --> 01:31:17.715 align:middle line:84%
anything that's
diminishing the fullness

01:31:17.715 --> 01:31:19.970 align:middle line:90%
and the power of who we are.

01:31:19.970 --> 01:31:23.870 align:middle line:84%
And then, it's allowing yourself
the space to have a dream,

01:31:23.870 --> 01:31:27.620 align:middle line:84%
have a vision, find
your inspiration.

01:31:27.620 --> 01:31:32.930 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the muses go around,
and they tap people for certain

01:31:32.930 --> 01:31:34.010 align:middle line:90%
things.

01:31:34.010 --> 01:31:38.740 align:middle line:84%
If you get tapped, and you have
an idea for something, do it.

01:31:38.740 --> 01:31:41.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Whatever our
soul's purpose here,

01:31:41.120 --> 01:31:42.770 align:middle line:84%
if you give it just
a little window,

01:31:42.770 --> 01:31:44.180 align:middle line:90%
it wants to burst through.

01:31:44.180 --> 01:31:47.484 align:middle line:90%
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

01:31:47.484 --> 01:31:51.260 align:middle line:90%


01:31:51.260 --> 01:31:53.330 align:middle line:90%
>> What makes your heart sing?

01:31:53.330 --> 01:31:55.230 align:middle line:90%
What sets you on fire?

01:31:55.230 --> 01:31:58.813 align:middle line:84%
What are you crazily
curious about?

01:31:58.813 --> 01:32:01.400 align:middle line:84%
And that fantasy, the
most far-reaching thing

01:32:01.400 --> 01:32:03.290 align:middle line:84%
that you really
want, but, you know,

01:32:03.290 --> 01:32:05.660 align:middle line:84%
your conscious mind is
telling you that, oh, well,

01:32:05.660 --> 01:32:07.908 align:middle line:84%
that's not practical,
and that takes hard work,

01:32:07.908 --> 01:32:09.950 align:middle line:84%
and it takes years, and
you have to go to school,

01:32:09.950 --> 01:32:11.908 align:middle line:84%
and all these other things
that are telling you

01:32:11.908 --> 01:32:15.120 align:middle line:84%
why it won't work-- ignore
them and just do it.

01:32:15.120 --> 01:32:17.870 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a really beautiful
idea that all we need

01:32:17.870 --> 01:32:21.120 align:middle line:84%
to actualize our soul's
purpose in this world,

01:32:21.120 --> 01:32:22.820 align:middle line:90%
all we need is the willingness.

01:32:22.820 --> 01:32:25.910 align:middle line:84%
All of the raw materials
will come to the surface

01:32:25.910 --> 01:32:29.300 align:middle line:84%
if we're just willing
to surrender and allow

01:32:29.300 --> 01:32:30.560 align:middle line:90%
that process to happen.

01:32:30.560 --> 01:32:32.600 align:middle line:84%
And just like a woman
is pregnant with a baby,

01:32:32.600 --> 01:32:34.920 align:middle line:84%
she's not thinking, oh, I
have to make the arm grow,

01:32:34.920 --> 01:32:37.610 align:middle line:84%
and now I have to make
the brain stem split

01:32:37.610 --> 01:32:38.960 align:middle line:90%
into the spinal cord.

01:32:38.960 --> 01:32:42.860 align:middle line:84%
She's just nourishing herself,
and so the baby is nurtured.

01:32:42.860 --> 01:32:46.260 align:middle line:84%
>> If you have that idea
and hold that space for it,

01:32:46.260 --> 01:32:47.060 align:middle line:90%
it will grow.

